<TITLE> 4 JMB men get 14 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com)  Chittagong divisional speedy trial tribunal Tuesday sentenced four JMB men to 14 years each in jail for possessing explosives. The convicted men are regional commander of JMB Chittagong Zabed Iqbal, Boma Mizan, Ayub Ali and Zahidul Islam. Judge Shafiqul Karim also ordered them to pay Tk 50,000 each in fines or serve out three more years in jail. The tribunal acquitted a fifth man Mashiur Rahman. The chargesheet accusing the five was submitted on Sept 5. RAB and Police seized explosives and arms from a house of Anwara Begum of Nur Para in Sadar Upazila in Cox's Bazar on August 20 in 2005. Two cases were filed with Sadar Police Station on the day. Boma Mizan is on the run. bdnews2
